__pycache__/
archive/
.omx/
.clawd-agents/
.playwright-cli/
output/
node_modules/
dist/
rust/target/
rust/server*.log
rust/server*.log.*.bak
rust/.claw-runtime/
apps/*/dist/
apps/*/node_modules/
apps/*/src-tauri/target/
# Tauri sidecar binaries — produced per-platform by
# .github/workflows/release.yml (cargo build --bin desktop-server →
# copied here with target-triple suffix). Per-build artifacts, never
# source. Local dev does not need them; tauri:dev still works without.
apps/*/src-tauri/binaries/
# Tauri ingest-pipeline resources (wechat_fetcher.py, defuddle_worker.js,
# markitdown_worker.py, package.json) staged from rust/crates/wiki_ingest/src/
# during the release workflow. Same rule: build artifact, not source.
apps/*/src-tauri/scripts/
*.tsbuildinfo
# Claude Code local artifacts
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/sessions/
.port_sessions/

# Project-local runtime state — may contain API keys / secrets, never commit.
# These are per-user configuration read by desktop-server at runtime:
#   settings.json      — active model, permission mode, etc.
#   providers.json     — multi-provider registry (Phase 3; will include
#                        api_key fields for DeepSeek/Qwen/Kimi/GLM/...)
#   plugins/installed/ — plugin manager working copy
#   desktop/           — persistence of sessions/scheduled tasks/dispatch
.claw/settings.json
.claw/settings.local.json
.claw/providers.json
.claw/plugins/installed/
.claw/desktop/
# Stale debugging file from earlier credential-routing experiments
.claude/settings.json

# Local data / runtime state / OS artifacts — never commit
# (See rules/trigger-map.md pre-commit checklist for the full list)
.clawwiki/
__MACOSX/
apps/desktop-shell/.claude/
llm-wiki/
rust/.claw/
rust/crates/wiki_ingest/src/package-lock.json
ClawWiki Design System/uploads/
